Moranbong band, however, returned on 7 September 2015 to perform in a concert attended by Kim Jong-un.

In August–September 2015, the band performed with the State Merited Chorus in two concerts in Moscow, Russia: at the Tchaikovsky Concert Hall on 31 August and at the Moskvich Cultural Center on 1 September.
On 11 October 2015, the band performed in the people's theater, Pyongyang on the occasion of the 70th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
They performed on 1 January 2016, in a New Year's concert at the People's Palace of Culture.
The Chongbong Band was formed in late July 2015.
However, the Moranbong Band reappeared on 7 September 2015, a week after the Chongbong Band made its public debut in Moscow, Russia.

In August–September 2015, the band performed with the State Merited Chorus in two concerts in Moscow, Russia: at the Tchaikovsky Concert Hall on 31 August and at the Moskvich Cultural Center on 1 September.
On the 19th of the same month, the Chongbong Band performed the same concert in front of Kim Jong-un and his wife Ri Sol-ju.
They performed on 1 January 2016, in a New Year's concert at the People's Palace of Culture.
